%erg v1
Title: Remove or replace git fsck --unreachable in housekeeping
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-27
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-27T12:30Z claude created

--- body ---
## Problem

Housekeeping runs `git fsck --unreachable` on every project at each beat.
On large repos this is expensive (scans all objects) and produces verbose
output that inflates the LLM context. Unreachable commits do not affect
correctness or workflow — they are cleaned up automatically by `git gc`
on its own schedule.

## Solution

Remove `git fsck --unreachable` from the housekeeping skill entirely.
If the intent was to flag dangling objects, replace with:

```bash
git gc --auto
```

`git gc --auto` runs only when thresholds are met (default: 6700 loose
objects or 50 packs) and produces no output when there is nothing to do.
It is idempotent and safe to call every run.

If there is no `git fsck` call in the current skill text, confirm by
grepping skills/housekeeping/ and close this ticket.

## Acceptance criteria

- `git fsck --unreachable` does not appear in any housekeeping skill file
- Either `git gc --auto` is present, or the decision to omit it entirely
  is documented in a skill comment
- Housekeeping runs produce no fsck output in their logs
